notes.noteText: Menu submitted for DM approval
Only changed a couple of small things.
Thank you Daniel for holding down the fort at Emery!  Great Job!
Menu approved by DM.  Menu submitted for RD approval

Hello! We're excited to partner with you in menu review with the goal of offering the best menu for your community while upholding the SAGE Way! We start our review by checking your exceptions in the client management tool. That tool is in the process of being updated to include more sections.  In the meantime, if there isn’t an appropriate spot for your exception, just list it at the top with the soups and we’ll see it. Then, we follow the Menu Review Checklist (located in the Media Library) and leave a note if we see anything missing. If we ask for something you don’t offer, please make sure your exceptions list is up to date.
I noticed that your changes to weeks 1-4 aren’t copied forward to future weeks. Please adjust.

Allergies: Thanks for getting your allergy list to us. I used the MB filter to ensure everyone with an allergy in your community has a variety of choices each day. Options look great! Don’t forget to follow recipes and Serve It Safely SOPs to avoid cross contact.

Local Ingredients: Just a reminder to adjust your menu throughout the cycle to include seasonal and local products.  Don’t forget to utilize our new Special Menu Item: “Featuring Local {Ingredient} from:” and the “Meet the Farmer” signs to show off our commitment to local sourcing.
Stock Exchange: On Mon Wk 1, you have vegetable broth menued as one of your soups. Is that intentional? If not, can you swap out for a vegetarian soup?
Stock Exchange: I see you have dairy days on Tues/Thurs. I noticed the broccoli-cheddar soup contains chicken broth on Tues Wk 1.

Improvisations: The tropical fruit salad you have menued on Fri Wk 1 is a recipe with specific ingredients that must be followed. If you would like more flexibility, consider changing this to Assorted Fresh-Cut Fruit.

Main Ingredient: The standard is to have 2 vegetables daily, including a steamed/plain (salt & pepper only) and a green-colored vegetable. These can be one and the same (for example: steamed broccoli meets both criteria). Please note that some recipes with steamed in the title do not meet the steamed/plain criteria because of additional ingredients. If in doubt, please check recipe tagging. Please add a steamed/plain vegetable on: Thurs Wk 1, Mon Wk 4
Main Ingredient: Please add a 2nd vegetable on: Wed Wk 1
Performance: A starch, protein, and veg pick should be offered daily. Please add a performance pick protein to Mon Wk 3, Thurs Wk 4
Performance: Gina, can you confirm that it is okay to have the performance plate split across multiple stations at this venue?

Seasonings: It is now required that you customize all Seasonings stations prior to menu approval. This is a new requirement after finding that production forms were not printing properly which caused problems during inspections. We also want to be sure that our online menus match what is in our dining hall to better serve our communities and those with food allergies. If you need help with this process, please see the Menu Builder Guide in the media library. Please customize: Vegetable Crudite Station, Chips & Dip Station, Chips & Salsa Bar, Educational Seasonings Got Gluten, Absolutely Sushi Station.
Seasonings: If you need help customizing your seasonings stations, please refer to the How Do I video at https://www.sagedining.com/intranet/apps/messages/?p=138136

Great work on the menu so far! Please scroll up to view all the notes and adjust your menu as needed. If we’ve asked for things that can’t be implemented in your venue, just leave us a note to let us know and update the exceptions tool so we’ll know not to ask again next time around.  We look forward to hearing back from you soon!   
~Jessica
Menu returned by RD/DM for corrections
Menu submitted for DM approval
Menu approved by DM.  Menu submitted for RD approval
I noticed that your changes to weeks 1-4 aren’t copied forward to future weeks. Please adjust. If these are all unique weeks, please let me know so that I can review the additional weeks.
Main Ingredient: We still need a steamed/plain veg on Mon Wk 4. If you want to use green beans, try recipe #31032.
Performance: Gina, can you confirm that it is okay to have the performance plate split across multiple stations at this venue?
Seasonings: The Educational Seasonings Got Gluten and Absolutely Sushi Station still need to be customized.

Thanks for the changes so far! Please scroll up for remaining comments. Also, you have empty cells throughout the menu - this is why some of the week tabs are gray. Please add "not serving" to these cells if you are not going to run that station on that day. I am not able to approve a menu with empty cells. Let me know if you have any questions! 
~Jessica
Menu returned by RD/DM for corrections
Menu submitted for DM approval
Hello, It's ok to have performance split across multiple stations, thanks!
Carl, I am going to approve this menu but according to the latest comments from your client, we need to revamp the menu for next year.  Thank you

Performance: You have designed your menu perfectly for athletes.  Awesome!  The icon will show on your menus and line signs.  If you make any changes to the menu that affect these performance pick items, you must replace them with another performance pick.  We must be sure athletes looking to use the recommendations can do so every day.
Main Ingredient: We still need a steamed/plain veg on Mon Wk 4. If you want to use green beans, try recipe #31032.
Seasonings: The Educational Seasonings Got Gluten station still needs to be customized. Are you serving the full list of options?

Thanks for the changes. There are still a couple things that need attention. Let me know if you have any questions.
~Jessica

~Jessica
